    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAppimage version used in 0.11 (AppImage runtime version: https://github.com/AppImage/type2-runtime/commit/2df896e) crashes when suspending or hibernating.\n\nThis is a known bug in runtime - https://github.com/AppImage/type2-runtime/issues/119\n\nThis doesn't happen with v0.10.4\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Install appimage\n2. Open nvim\n3. Hibernate/suspend\n4. See terminal\n5. `zsh: bus error nvim`\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMaybe neovim can make some workaround until this issue is fixed there?\n\nA [commenter there mentioned](https://github.com/pkgforge-dev/ghostty-appimage/issues/27#issuecomment-2693882775) they switched to a different runtime\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian 12\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
